    {
      "agency": "OCFA",
      "time_iso": "2026-05-28T02:30:00Z",
      "text": "There is no longer a threat of explosion, fire or chemical leak for the damaged tank at the GKN Aerospace facility in Garden Grove. County health officials, fire crews and the Environmental Protection Agency all confirmed that there is no chemical leak, threat of explosion, threat of fire, or risk to the public in connection with the chemical incident in Garden Grove.",
      "source_url": "https://abc7.com/live-updates/garden-grove-chemical-tank-emergency-leaking-toxic-chemicals-orange-county-will-spill-explode-officials-say/19152918/"
    },
    {
      "agency": "US EPA \u2014 on-scene coordinator Chris Myers",
      "time_iso": "2026-05-28T02:00:00Z",
      "text": "No exceedances have been detected at any time throughout this event, and air monitoring will continue. There was no contamination. There were no fumes. There were no vapors that came from this incident.",
      "source_url": "https://abc7.com/live-updates/garden-grove-chemical-tank-emergency-leaking-toxic-chemicals-orange-county-will-spill-explode-officials-say/19152918/"
